OL,6,F"The BBC said that it supplied
OL,7,Fextensive evidence to the court of the
OL,8,Fcareful editorial process, and it was
OL,9,Faccepted and conceded by Gerry Adams'
OL,10,Flegal team that the broadcast and
OL,11,Fpublication were in the highest public
OL,12,Finterest.
OL,14,F"They clearly felt they had no option
OL,15,Fbut to defend their journalism."
OL,17,FDespite losing the case, BBC
OL,18,Fjournalist Jennifer O'Leary said: "I
OL,19,Fhad nothing to hide, only sources to
OL,20,Fprotect, and I want to thank them for
OL,21,Ftrusting me".
